<div id="review_2803777712" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2803777712" />
    <a title="Petty Lisbon " class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/34227480-petty-lisbon"><img alt="Petty Lisbon " src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1473624965p2/34227480.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2803777712?book_show_action=true">Apr 29, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Petty Lisbon " class="user" itemprop="url" name="Petty Lisbon " href="/user/show/34227480-petty-lisbon">Petty Lisbon </a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780805089646" href="/book/show/6387913-pedro-and-me">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/34227480-petty-lisbon?shelf=tv-is-my-friend">tv-is-my-friend</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2803777712" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1326862033700153121">Maybe it&apos;s because I&apos;ve been treating reading as a chore lately, but this book hit me right in the gut. I read my fair share of graphic novels and comic books (although for whatever reasons, I don&apos;t mark the Riverdale ones on here), but this one showed me the storytelling potential of this medium. I haven&apos;t seen Season 3 of The Real World yet but I&apos;ve read about Pedro&apos;s story, and even if you already know about him, reading all about it from a close friend instead of just Wikipedia makes it so m</span>
  <span id="freeText1326862033700153121" style="display:none">Maybe it's because I've been treating reading as a chore lately, but this book hit me right in the gut. I read my fair share of graphic novels and comic books (although for whatever reasons, I don't mark the Riverdale ones on here), but this one showed me the storytelling potential of this medium. I haven't seen Season 3 of The Real World yet but I've read about Pedro's story, and even if you already know about him, reading all about it from a close friend instead of just Wikipedia makes it so much more emotional. I definitely recommend it.</span>
  <a data-text-id="1326862033700153121" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

<tr class="no_border feedFooterReview" id="update_comment_stuff_Review2803777712">
