<div id="review_93182645" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/93182645" />
    <a title="Ms. D" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1432692-ms-d"><img alt="Ms. D" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1221523108p2/1432692.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/93182645?book_show_action=true">Mar 08, 2010</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ms. D" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ms. D" href="/user/show/1432692-ms-d">Ms. D</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780805089646" href="/book/show/6387913-pedro-and-me">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1432692-ms-d?shelf=non-fiction">non-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1432692-ms-d?shelf=memoirs">memoirs</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1432692-ms-d?shelf=graphic-texts">graphic-texts</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer93182645" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8751816488592824847">In the beginning, before The Hills and Jersey Shore, there was quality reality TV. (Seems like an oxymoron now.) For instance, The Real World, San Francisco. (And no, Sade, the show wasn&apos;t in black and white, but it did air before you were born, in 1994.) This graphic novel is written by one of the &quot;seven strangers&quot; on that show, about his roommate and friend Pedro Zamora. Pedro was an AIDS activist and educator who probably did more to raise awareness than anyone at his time or since. As Presid</span>
  <span id="freeText8751816488592824847" style="display:none">In the beginning, before The Hills and Jersey Shore, there was quality reality TV. (Seems like an oxymoron now.) For instance, The Real World, San Francisco. (And no, Sade, the show wasn't in black and white, but it did air before you were born, in 1994.) This graphic novel is written by one of the "seven strangers" on that show, about his roommate and friend Pedro Zamora. Pedro was an AIDS activist and educator who probably did more to raise awareness than anyone at his time or since. As President Clinton said, "Now none of us can say that we don't know anyone living with AIDS." I think that anyone who remembers the show and Pedro would appreciate this funny, touching tribute. And I'd recommend it to those of my students who like graphic novels, or memoirs, or just good books. I'm curious to know what you think. And how you think Judd and Pedro compare to Heidi Montag and The Situation...</span>
  <a data-text-id="8751816488592824847" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


